00:31:35,827 --> 00:31:37,096
It's an intangible.

1084
00:31:37,196 --> 00:31:37,930
-Well, thanks, Johnny.

1085
00:31:38,030 --> 00:31:38,730
But you got it, too.

1086
00:31:38,830 --> 00:31:39,865
Anybody has.

1087
00:31:39,966 --> 00:31:40,666
-Nah.

1088
00:31:40,766 --> 00:31:42,068
I went to Catholic school.

1089
00:31:42,168 --> 00:31:44,136
I was an altar boy.

1090
00:31:44,236 --> 00:31:45,604
I never looked
death in the face.

1091
00:31:48,941 --> 00:31:51,043
-What makes you think I did?

1092
00:31:51,143 --> 00:31:54,446
-I don't know, a feeling.

1093
00:31:54,546 --> 00:31:56,182
Armand, I-- I need
something real.

1094
00:31:56,282 --> 00:31:59,385
I need something as
ancient and as Italian

1095
00:31:59,485 --> 00:32:04,023
as-- as this clove
of garlic here.

1096
00:32:04,123 --> 00:32:04,991
-All right.
All right.

1097
00:32:05,091 --> 00:32:05,992
Hey.
Hey, we'll start right there.

1098
00:32:06,092 --> 00:32:07,259
-What?

1099
00:32:07,359 --> 00:32:09,261
-You slice the garlic, you
help me make a sauce, huh?

1100
00:32:09,361 --> 00:32:10,596
What could be deeper than that?

1101
00:32:10,696 --> 00:32:11,530
Here.

1102
00:32:11,630 --> 00:32:12,664
-You serious?

1103
00:32:12,764 --> 00:32:13,932
-Yeah.

1104
00:32:14,033 --> 00:32:16,268
Come on, smell this.

1105
00:32:16,368 --> 00:32:19,471
That's the power of
your tradition, right?

1106
00:32:19,571 --> 00:32:21,507
Come on, slice it up.

1107
00:32:21,607 --> 00:32:24,576
Got to connect with
the swirls, right?

1108
00:32:24,676 --> 00:32:27,946
Connect with these swirls.

1109
00:32:28,047 --> 00:32:28,847
-Ah.

1110
00:32:28,947 --> 00:32:31,650
Ooh, I cut myself.

1111
00:32:31,750 --> 00:32:33,019
-Hey, well, there you go.

1112
00:32:33,119 --> 00:32:34,520
Hey, real blood, huh?

1113
00:32:34,620 --> 00:32:35,587
Now we're talking.

1114
00:32:35,687 --> 00:32:36,155
-Oh.

1115
00:32:36,255 --> 00:32:36,822
What the hell?

1116
00:32:36,922 --> 00:32:37,990
Am I out of my mind?

1117
00:32:38,090 --> 00:32:39,925
I'm talking to a demented
Wolfgang Puck here.

1118
00:32:40,026 --> 00:32:40,726
-Hey, Johnny.

1119
00:32:40,826 --> 00:32:42,628
Can you get me in to read?

1120
00:32:42,728 --> 00:32:44,463
-What?

1121
00:32:44,563 --> 00:32:46,798
-Well, you say I
got Sicilian swirls.

1122
00:32:46,898 --> 00:32:48,034
There's got to be
other parts, right?

1123
00:32:48,134 --> 00:32:49,968
Other Sicilian swirlers, right?

1124
00:32:50,069 --> 00:32:51,303
-Ah, what a business.

1125
00:32:51,403 --> 00:32:52,571
All right, Armand.

1126
00:32:52,671 --> 00:32:54,373
I mean, if I get in the
door, I'll see what I can do.

1127
00:32:54,473 --> 00:32:55,407
Now, come on, Armand.

1128
00:32:55,507 --> 00:32:56,475
I need your help.

1129
00:32:56,575 --> 00:32:59,311
-All right, I'll tell
you what I think.

1130
00:32:59,411 --> 00:33:01,647
The guys with real balls,
they never show it.

1131
00:33:01,747 --> 00:33:03,749
The scariest guy I ever met,
he looked like the grocer

1132
00:33:03,849 --> 00:33:04,750
down the street.

1133
00:33:04,850 --> 00:33:06,352
He blended in like
your average Joe.

1134
00:33:06,452 --> 00:33:10,089
But if you ever looked into
his eyes, he didn't blink.

1135
00:33:10,189 --> 00:33:11,957
It was like looking in
to the eyes of a shark.

1136
00:33:12,058 --> 00:33:13,159
They-- they were dead eyes.

1137
00:33:18,497 --> 00:33:19,298
-Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

1138
00:33:19,398 --> 00:33:21,867
That's good.

1139
00:33:21,967 --> 00:33:25,337
-Quiet and calm, dead eyes.

1140
00:33:25,437 --> 00:33:26,305
-Right.

1141
00:33:26,405 --> 00:33:27,773
Right.

1142
00:33:27,873 --> 00:33:28,940
Dead eyes.

1143
00:33:29,041 --> 00:33:29,775
-Right.

1144
00:33:29,875 --> 00:33:32,044
All right, let's give it a shot.

1145
00:33:36,048 --> 00:33:37,083
That's it.

1146
00:33:37,183 --> 00:33:38,917
That's it.

1147
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:40,986
Feel it.

1148
00:33:41,087 --> 00:33:41,787
Good.

1149
00:33:41,887 --> 00:33:42,621
Good.

1150
00:33:42,721 --> 00:33:43,822
Yeah.

1151
00:33:43,922 --> 00:33:45,424
You know, your hair is
perfect for this, Johnny.

1152
00:33:45,524 --> 00:33:49,561
You're going to have to lose
about 50 pounds, though.

1153
00:33:49,661 --> 00:33:51,763
So is Rudy Ptak up for the role?

1154
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:53,499
-You had to mention
his friggin name?

1155
00:33:53,599 --> 00:33:56,202
-Hey, come on.

1156
00:33:56,302 --> 00:33:59,171
Use your anger.

1157
00:33:59,271 --> 00:34:00,672
That's it.

1158
00:34:00,772 --> 00:34:04,143
You're doing it.

1159
00:34:04,243 --> 00:34:07,146
[dog barking]

1160
00:34:21,193 --> 00:34:23,562
[dog crying]

1161
00:34:28,867 --> 00:34:32,204
-My life is like some weird
cosmic test, you know?

1162
00:34:32,304 --> 00:34:34,406
I haven't worked in
a year and a half.

1163
00:34:34,506 --> 00:34:36,975
You know, if God has
given me all this talent,

1164
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:39,945
why doesn't he give
me a way to use it?

1165
00:34:40,045 --> 00:34:41,046
It's a curse.

1166
00:34:41,147 --> 00:34:42,548
It's a punishment.

1167
00:34:42,648 --> 00:34:43,549
-A punishment?

1168
00:34:43,649 --> 00:34:46,051
For what?

1169
00:34:46,152 --> 00:34:47,586
-I don't want to do this, OK?

1170
00:34:47,686 --> 00:34:48,954
-No, look.

1171
00:34:49,054 --> 00:34:51,123
I think-- why don't you try to
go up for this Capone thing?

1172
00:34:51,223 --> 00:34:53,459
-Because it's a
secret thing, OK?

1173
00:34:53,559 --> 00:34:56,428
And I-- I wouldn't cross Johnny.

1174
00:34:56,528 --> 00:34:58,164
-You're an actor just
like everyone else.

1175
00:34:58,264 --> 00:34:59,798
Why shouldn't you go up for it?

1176
00:34:59,898 --> 00:35:02,668
-Because I wouldn't do
a thing like that, OK?

1177
00:35:02,768 --> 00:35:03,469
End of story.

1178
00:35:09,341 --> 00:35:14,413
[car honking]

1179
00:35:14,513 --> 00:35:15,214
-Jo.

1180
00:35:15,314 --> 00:35:16,515
You forget I needed the car?

1181
00:35:16,615 --> 00:35:17,783
That audition's in 20 minutes.

1182
00:35:17,883 --> 00:35:18,584
-No.

1183
00:35:18,684 --> 00:35:19,585
I didn't forget.

1184
00:35:19,685 --> 00:35:20,586
-You didn't?

1185
00:35:20,686 --> 00:35:21,653
So what-- what happened?

1186
00:35:21,753 --> 00:35:22,721
-Nothing.

1187
00:35:22,821 --> 00:35:23,522
I'm sorry.

1188
00:35:23,622 --> 00:35:24,055
-Jo?

1189
00:35:24,156 --> 00:35:24,890
-Good luck.

1190
00:35:24,990 --> 00:35:26,692
-Jo, don't do this to me, OK?

1191
00:35:26,792 --> 00:35:27,759
What's happening?

1192
00:35:27,859 --> 00:35:28,860
Will you tell me what's
going on, please?

1193
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:29,661
-OK.

1194
00:35:29,761 --> 00:35:30,696
I had to go to the bank.

1195
00:35:30,796 --> 00:35:31,730
We bounced another check.

1196
00:35:31,830 --> 00:35:34,466
-Oh, no.

1197
00:35:34,566 --> 00:35:35,667
Who was it this time?

1198
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:44,410
We bounced a check on my mother?

1199
00:35:48,547 --> 00:35:50,949
-Johnny DiMartino
for the Casper's

1200
00:35:51,049 --> 00:35:55,454
