1201
00:35:55,554 --> 00:35:56,988
This is my father.

1202
00:35:57,088 --> 00:35:59,491
He comes with me.

1203
00:35:59,591 --> 00:36:00,859
-Oh, right.

1204
00:36:00,959 --> 00:36:02,694
You're on the list.

1205
00:36:02,794 --> 00:36:03,829
-Hey, you're late.

1206
00:36:03,929 --> 00:36:05,364
What the hell happened?

1207
00:36:05,464 --> 00:36:06,164
-We got hung up.

1208
00:36:13,905 --> 00:36:15,040
-OK.

1209
00:36:15,140 --> 00:36:17,976
I'm going to need you
right here, right in tight.

1210
00:36:18,076 --> 00:36:20,279
And when I say
action, then you go.

1211
00:36:20,379 --> 00:36:21,146
I love the sweatshirt.

1212
00:36:21,247 --> 00:36:22,214
It's a nice touch.

1213
00:36:22,314 --> 00:36:24,683
-Thank you.

1214
00:36:24,783 --> 00:36:25,484
-OK.

1215
00:36:25,584 --> 00:36:26,318
And action.

1216
00:36:26,418 --> 00:36:27,085
-Why are you breathing so hard?

1217
00:36:27,185 --> 00:36:28,987
What's the matter with you?

1218
00:36:29,087 --> 00:36:32,858
I just dropped two-thirds of
my fat and half my calories.

1219
00:36:32,958 --> 00:36:35,594
-Two-thirds of your fat
and half your calories?

1220
00:36:35,694 --> 00:36:36,595
That's wonderful, sir.

1221
00:36:36,695 --> 00:36:38,764
-Um, Tony, right?

1222
00:36:38,864 --> 00:36:39,665
JOHNNY: Johnny.

1223
00:36:39,765 --> 00:36:40,599
-OK.

1224
00:36:40,699 --> 00:36:41,867
The idea of doing
it like Scarface

1225
00:36:41,967 --> 00:36:43,335
is interesting, sort of.

1226
00:36:43,435 --> 00:36:45,904
But this is an
upstairs/downstairs thing.

1227
00:36:46,004 --> 00:36:47,773
The bun is the
schlepper who's been

1228
00:36:47,873 --> 00:36:49,241
carrying the hot
dog like forever.

1229
00:36:49,341 --> 00:36:50,041
-Aha.

1230
00:36:50,141 --> 00:36:51,209
-So you're-- yeah.

1231
00:36:51,310 --> 00:36:53,312
So you're more of a
swelled head poshon, dig?

1232
00:36:53,412 --> 00:36:56,315
Think John Goodman in pink
tights, but not too shitcky.

1233
00:36:56,415 --> 00:36:59,385
We want a little Larry Sanders
reality thing to it, too.

1234
00:36:59,485 --> 00:37:00,185
You dig?

1235
00:37:00,286 --> 00:37:00,986
-Not too shitcky.

1236
00:37:06,692 --> 00:37:08,860
STEVE: What are you doing?

1237
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:09,695
-Hm?

1238
00:37:09,795 --> 00:37:10,796
-What are you doing?

1239
00:37:10,896 --> 00:37:11,597
-What?

1240
00:37:11,697 --> 00:37:12,698
-That thing with your eyes.

1241
00:37:12,798 --> 00:37:13,732
What are you doing?

1242
00:37:13,832 --> 00:37:14,566
Stop it, Johnny.

1243
00:37:14,666 --> 00:37:15,667
You're blowing this job for me.

1244
00:37:15,767 --> 00:37:16,668
I need it.

1245
00:37:16,768 --> 00:37:18,504
Snap out of it.

1246
00:37:18,604 --> 00:37:19,505
-Oh, uh, sorry.

1247
00:37:19,605 --> 00:37:20,306
Stevie.

1248
00:37:20,406 --> 00:37:21,172
Hey, Trent.

1249
00:37:21,273 --> 00:37:21,973
Trent, look.

1250
00:37:22,073 --> 00:37:22,641
I'm sorry.

1251
00:37:22,741 --> 00:37:23,442
I was trying something.

1252
00:37:23,542 --> 00:37:24,710
It didn't work.

1253
00:37:24,810 --> 00:37:26,778
Uh, Larry Sanders
via the Flintstones

1254
00:37:26,878 --> 00:37:28,046
but not too shticky.

1255
00:37:28,146 --> 00:37:29,581
It's a beautiful concept, Trent.

1256
00:37:29,681 --> 00:37:30,949
-Let's do it.
-Very Spielbergian.

1257
00:37:31,049 --> 00:37:31,750
-Thanks.

1258
00:37:31,850 --> 00:37:33,184
Uh, Johnny, listen.

1259
00:37:33,285 --> 00:37:35,220
Uh, the original
idea was to go with

